dustry and academic placements. Open the panels below to see a selection of the companies, agencies, and universities that represented their first destinations after UIC.       destinations     Industry roles         industry    Aldea Services  ANSYS  ARCADIS  Apple  Argonne National Laboratory  Boston Consulting Group  Brooms Engineering  Burns and McDonnell  CDM Smith  Christopher B. Burke Engineering  Chicago Transportation Authority (CTA)  Concrete Reinforcing Steel Institute  CTL Group  ENGEO Inc.  Environmental Information Logistics, LLC  Exponent Inc.  EY (Ernst & Young)  Federal Aviation Authority  Federal Energy Regulatory Commission  FICOSA Inc.  Ford Motor Co. Autonomous Driving Research Laboratory  Foster Wheeler  Freeport McRoRan  Frontrunner Systems Inc.  Geosyntec Consultants  GSG Consultants  HERE  IBI Group  Illinois Department of Transportation  Integrity Structural Corp.  Intel  Interra Inc.  IQA Solutions  Jacobs Engineering Group  JD.com R&D Center  John Deere  Kiewit Corporation  KPMG  Lawrence-Livermore National Laboratory  Marriott International  McDermott  Metropolitan Washington Council of Governments  Mistras Group Inc.  Motorola  MWH Engineering  Omega & Associates  Otsuka Pharmaceutical Company  PCA StructurePoint  RGE Engineering  RK&K  RS&H  Sam Consultants Inc.  Science Tomorrow  SK Ghosh & Associates  Skanska  Skidmore, Owings, and Merrill  Sovereign Investment Fund of Denmark  Spirit Airlines  Stewart Inc.  Terracon Consultants Inc.  Thornton Tomasetti  Tucson Metropolitan Planning Organization  Turner Construction  URS Corporation, Canada  U.S. Army Corps of Engineers  U.S. Army Research Laboratory  Vitagora, France  WSP USA  84.51˚         Academic positions and further study         academia    Anna University, India  Arizona State University  California State University  Colorado School of Mines  Georgia Institute of Technology  Hacettepe University, Turkey  Illinois Institute of Technology  Japan Research Institute  Johns Hopki